data.name: Cepsa Chemicals
data.description:
At Cepsa Chemicals we make chemistry for a better world. Our products are present in the daily lives of millions of people worldwide and in the value chain of almost all industrial sectors. In addition, we favor a circular economy that optimizes the use of resources to build a more sustainable, efficient, and fair world.

Our products and processes have the guarantee of Leadership, Innovation, and Sustainability.

INTERNATIONAL LEADERS

We are the world's leading producer of alkylbenzene, a raw material for manufacturing biodegradable detergents. We are also the world’s leading producer of Cumene and second in Phenol and Acetone.

INNOVATIVE PROJECTS

We are committed to continuous improvement to provide value to our customers, and we rely on innovation to develop our business.

SUSTAINABLE GROWTH

We do not understand chemicals without sustainability, which is why we are committed to continuous improvement in areas such as Safety, Health and the Environment.

data.name: CepSinol®
data.description: CepSinol® product portfolio comprises a vast range of pure cuts as well as the most common used blends of fatty alcohols produced from plant sources such as palm kernel oil and find application in various home and personal care applications as well as in flavors&fragances, agriculture, crude oil exploration, paints and coatings, emulsion polymerization, pharma, pulp and paper, lubricants, and textile auxiliaries among others.All CepSinol® products are available in RSPO Mass Balance certified form.

data.name: NextPhenol
data.description: NextPhenol is a hydroxybenzene that incorporates certified secondary raw materials from biomass / industrial waste or renewable raw materials and maintains the same technical specifications as its fossil counterpart. new NextPhenol is a range of sustainable products, which have the same quality levels as their fossil counterpart while reducing their environmental impact.

data.name: CepSinol® - e
data.description: CepSinol® - e product portfolio includes an extensive range of fatty alcohol ethoxylates that show excellent wetting properties, having low foam, and being effective even at low temperatures. They are the best surfactants for greasy soils and exhibit outstanding compatibility with all the ingredients used in detergent. It is less sensitive to water hardness and can easily achieve the higher concentrations needed in some formats.

data.name: CepSinol® - es
data.description: CepSinol®-es surfactants show high surface activity, high foam ability, good viscosity response, low irritation property and excellent hard-water resistance. They are readily biodegradable and can be easily formulated with other surfactants, and it provides a good synergistic effect with other ingredients like enzymes.

data.name: CepSinol® - s
data.description: CepSinol®-s surfactants are strong cleaning agents used as a primary surfactant in household and industrial cleaning applications. It is also used in personal care products and can be easily formulated with other surfactants. CepSinol®-s surfactants have a good flash foaming property, are biodegradable and are used in personal care products such as toothpastes as well as household and industrial cleaning end uses.

data.name: CepSinol® 1214
data.description: CepSinol® 1214 is a fatty alcohol blend, representing an essential industrial intermediate. These fatty alcohols, like their pure-cut counterparts, can be readily converted into derivatives used in a diverse array of applications across industries, encompassing home and personal care products, fragrances and flavors, the petroleum sector, metalworking, lubricants, and agricultural chemicals.

data.name: CepSinol® (MB*) P10

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Capric Alcohol, Caprinic Alcohol, Decanol, Decanol-(1), Decyl Alcohol, Decyl N-Alcohol, N-Decan-1-ol, N-Decanol, N-Decyl Alcohol, Nonylcarbinol

data.description: CepSinol® (MB*) P10 is a pure-cut fatty alcohol with a wide range of industrial applications. These fatty alcohols serve as key intermediates that can be further processed and converted into various derivatives. These derivatives find applications in a broad spectrum of products and industries, including home and personal care products, fragrances, flavors, the petroleum industry, metalworking, lubricants, and agricultural chemicals. These pure-cut fatty alcohols play a crucial role in the formulation and production of a diverse range of consumer and industrial goods.

data.name: CepSinol® 1218
data.description: CepSinol® 1218 is a fatty alcohol blend serving as a fundamental industrial intermediate. These fatty alcohols, whether in pure cut or blended forms, can be easily converted into derivatives utilized across a wide range of applications in sectors such as home and personal care products, fragrances and flavors, the petroleum industry, metalworking, lubricants, and agricultural chemicals.

data.name: RECODAS 185
data.description: RECODAS 185 is a surfactant designed for enhanced oil recovery (EOR) and is predominantly composed of dialkylbenzene sodium sulfonates. It is formulated to achieve ultra-low interfacial tension (IFT) when used in the alkaline surfactant polymer (ASP) and surfactant polymer (SP) methods. It is typically used alongside co-surfactants or co-solvents in EOR formulations.

data.name: NEXTLAB R550-L
data.description: NEXTLAB R550-L, much like its counterpart, PETRELAB 550, incorporates certified renewable materials, maintaining identical specifications. It serves as a vital raw material for manufacturing linear alkylbenzene sulfonic acid (LABSA) through sulfonation, which is then neutralized into linear alkylbenzene sulfonate (LAS). LAS functions as a prominent anionic surfactant, widely used in household detergents such as laundry powders, liquid detergents, dishwashing products, multipurpose cleaners, and various other applications across different industries.

data.name: PETREPAR® n-C10
data.description: PETREPAR® n-C10 is a linear alkane hydrocarbon with a content exceeding 95% in n-decane. This substance has diverse applications, serving as a solvent in printing inks, degreasers, drilling oils, lubricants, herbicides, and insecticides. It is characterized by its degreasing capabilities and high solvency. It is prevalent in markets related to agriculture and feed, HI&I care, industrial care, and personal care.

data.name: CepSinol® - e (MB*) 1214/1
data.description: CepSinol® - e (MB*) 1214/1 is a fatty alcohol with a relatively low ethylene oxide content, which results in low solubility in water. It is primarily utilized in the production of ethoxy-sulfated alcohols. These ethoxy-sulfated alcohols, when they contain a higher ethylene oxide content, become water-soluble and are directly employed as non-ionic surfactants in various applications. This versatile range of surfactants finds use in a wide array of products, including laundry detergents, household cleaners, industrial and institutional cleaning formulations, and applications related to agriculture, textiles, and the oil industry. These surfactants play a critical role in enhancing the performance and cleaning properties of these products.

data.name: Cepsa Chemicals Cumene

summary.name: Synonyms
items: (1-Methylethyl)-Benzene, (Methylethyl)benzene, (Propan-2-yl)benzene, 1-Methylethyl-Benzene, 2-Fenyl-propaan, 2-Phenyl propane, Benzene,Isopropyl Cumol, Cumol, i-Propyl-Benzene, Isopropyl Benzene, Isopropylbenzol

data.description: Cepsa Chemicals Cumene is produced through the catalytic alkylation of benzene with propylene. Both raw materials are derived from crude oil distillation. The bulk of cumene production is typically transformed into cumene hydroperoxide, an intermediate in the synthesis of essential chemicals like phenol and acetone. Additionally, cumene is used in surfactants, the production of propylene Oxide (PO), and as an additive in gasoline.

data.name: PETROSOL D 20/26
data.description: PETROSOL D 20/26 is a fraction of hydrogenated kerosene, with an initial and final distillation range typically between 200°C and 260°C. Notably, it exhibits very low aromatic content and has a faint odor. Its low aromatic content and nearly imperceptible scent make it a versatile choice for various applications, including use in paints, varnishes, fuel, solvents, lubricants, multipurpose oils, drilling fluids, insecticides, home air fresheners, and as an efficient degreaser.

data.seo_description: Knowde is the first marketplace for chemicals, polymers and ingredients. Our leading-edge digital capabilities connect thousands of sellers and buyers every day.

data.name: PETROSOL 15A 15/20
data.description: PETROSOL 15A 15/20 is a kerosene fraction with a typical initial and final distillation range spanning from 150°C to 200°C, and it maintains a low aromatic content. Its applications extend to various industries, particularly in the production of solvents, adhesives, paints, varnishes, and inks. It's primarily prevalent in the paints and coatings market.

data.name: PETROSOL D 40
data.description: PETROSOL D 40 is a hydrogenated naphtha-kerosene blend featuring a typical distillation range between 150 and 200°C. This product boasts an exceptionally low aromatic content and a barely discernible odor. Due to its minimal aromatic content and nearly odorless nature, PETROSOL D 40 finds application in various industries, including paint and varnish production, as a fuel source, a versatile solvent, a component in lubricants and multipurpose oils, drilling fluid formulations, insecticides, home air fresheners, and as an effective degreaser.

data.name: PETROSOL D 60
data.description: PETROSOL D 60 is a hydrogenated naphtha-kerosene blend featuring a typical distillation range of 190–220 °C. This product is distinguished by its remarkably low aromatic content and faint odor. Due to its low aromatic content and almost imperceptible scent, it serves various purposes, such as in the production of paints and varnishes, as a fuel source, a versatile solvent, a component in lubricants and multipurpose oils, drilling fluid formulations, insecticides, and home air fresheners, as well as an effective degreaser.

data.name: PETROSOL D 80
data.description: PETROSOL D 80 is a hydrogenated naphtha-kerosene blend with a typical flash point greater than or equal to 72ºC. It stands out for its low aromatic and sulfur content and faint odor. Just like its counterparts, PETROSOL D 80 is indispensable in various industries, including paint and varnish manufacturing, as a fuel source, a versatile solvent, a component in lubricants and multipurpose oils, drilling fluid formulations, insecticides, home air fresheners, and as an efficient degreaser.

data.name: PETROSOL D 100
data.description: PETROSOL D 100 is a hydrogenated naphtha-kerosene blend characterized by a typical distillation range of 240-270ºC. This product is recognized for its extremely low aromatic content and mild odor. Like PETROSOL D 60, its low aromatic content and subtle aroma make it a valuable asset in applications ranging from paint and varnish production to fuel, solvents, lubricants, drilling fluids, insecticides, home air fresheners, and degreasers.

data.name: PETROSOL 95A Xylene
data.description: PETROSOL 95A Xylene is an aromatic solvent composed of a mixture of xylene isomers. It is primarily used in adhesives and paints due to its moderate rate of evaporation. Furthermore, it is sulfonated and neutralized for the production of surfactants utilized in industrial and household cleaning products.

data.name: PETROSOL 95A 16/18
data.description: PETROSOL 95A 16/18 is a mixture of aromatic hydrocarbons, primarily C9-C10, with a typical initial and final distillation range between 160°C and 180°C. Its impressive solvent power makes it a valuable component in adhesives and paints, particularly noteworthy for its low cumene content. This product is mainly found in the Agriculture & Feed and HI&I Care markets.

data.name: PETROSOL 95A 18/20
data.description: PETROSOL 95A 18/20 is a liquid mixture composed primarily of aromatic hydrocarbons, primarily falling within the C9-C11 range, with a predominant presence of C10 compounds. It features a distillation range that typically spans from 180 to 200ºC. Thanks to its outstanding solvent capabilities, this substance finds application in the formulation of adhesives and paints, where it serves as a valuable component. Classified under the hydrocarbon product family, it offers versatility in various industrial applications.

data.name: PETROSOL 95A 18/20 ND
data.description: PETROSOL 95A 18/20 ND is a mixture of aromatic hydrocarbons, primarily consisting of C9-C11, with a predominant presence of C10. It has a typical initial and final distillation range of 180–200 oC and a low naphthalene content. Due to its impressive solvent capabilities, it is widely used in adhesives and paints.

data.name: PETROSOL 95A Toluene

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 1-Methylbenzene, Methyl-Benzene, Methylbenzol, Monomethyl Benzene, Phenyl-Methane, Phenylmethane

data.description: PETROSOL 95A Toluene is an aromatic solvent of high purity, with a minimum purity level of 99.8%. Its primary applications are in adhesives and paints, primarily due to its moderate rate of evaporation. It also plays a role in the synthesis of intermediates such as benzoic acid and benzaldehyde and serves as a raw material for the production of toluene diisocyanate and trinitrotoluene.

data.name: PETROSOL D 100/120
data.description: PETROSOL D 100/120 is a hydrocarbon consisting of normal and isoparaffins, along with naphthenes, and it typically exhibits an initial and final distillation range between 100°C and 120°C. This substance has a low aromatic content and serves as a solvent in various applications, including adhesives, paints, coatings, and silicones. It is also utilized as a degreaser and as a fluid in polymerization reactions.

data.name: PETROSOL D 20/26
data.description: PETROSOL D 20/26 is a fraction of hydrogenated kerosene, with an initial and final distillation range typically between 200°C and 260°C. Notably, it exhibits very low aromatic content and has a faint odor. Its low aromatic content and nearly imperceptible scent make it a versatile choice for various applications, including use in paints, varnishes, fuel, solvents, lubricants, multipurpose oils, drilling fluids, insecticides, home air fresheners, and as an efficient degreaser.

data.name: PETROSOL D Heptane
data.description: PETROSOL D Heptane is a mixture of normal, iso-, and cyclo-paraffin C7 hydrocarbons with a content exceeding 95%. It is primarily recognized as a solvent with minimal aromatics and impurities, along with a subtle scent. This versatile product finds applications in adhesives, paints, coatings, silicones, degreasing processes, and is also utilized for oil extraction in the food industry as well as a fluid in polymerization reactions.

data.name: PETROSOL D Hexane
data.description: PETROSOL D Hexane is a blend of n-hexane and its isomers, known for its volatility and rapid evaporation, coupled with a minimal aromatic content and a mild odor. Its principal application is in the food industry due to its excellent oil extraction capabilities. Moreover, it serves as a solvent in adhesives and paints and is an effective degreaser in various industrial processes.

data.name: PETROSOL D Isohexane
data.description: PETROSOL D Isohexane is a blend of C6 isomers with a n-hexane content below 5%. It stands out for its excellent volatility and rapid evaporation, coupled with minimal aromatics and impurities and a faint scent. It serves as a highly effective volatile solvent with versatile applications in various industries.
